@media (max-width: 640px) {
  .stats-row { grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr); }
  .assumption-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
  .verdict-card { padding: 32px 20px; }
}
</style>

<div class="header">
  <div class="header-content">
    <div class="tag">Original Research</div>
    <div class="tag">Compiled by Gemini 3.1</div>
    <h1>S&P Global (SPGI)<br/>Intrinsic Value</h1>
    <p class="subtitle">A transparent, two-stage discounted cash flow valuation of S&P Global Inc. — using actuals, disclosed assumptions, and one final number.</p>
    <p class="date">Updated March 18, 2026 · Data: Most Recent Fiscal Year | 10Y Treasury: 4.18%</p>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="container">
  {hasData ? (
  <>
  <!-- ═══ THE VERDICT ═══ -->
  <div class="verdict-card">
    <div class="verdict-label">Estimated Intrinsic Value Per Share</div>
    <div class="verdict-price">${roundedIV.toFixed(2)}</div>
    <div class="verdict-vs">vs. market price of ${currentPrice?.toFixed(2)} ({marginOfSafety}%)</div>
    <div class="verdict-badge" style={`background: ${verdictColor}22; color: ${verdictColor}; border: 1px solid ${verdictColor}44;`}>
      {verdictText}
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- ═══ KEY METRICS ═══ -->
  <div class="stats-row">
    <div class="stat-card">
      <div class="stat-value">${revCurrent !== null ? (revCurrent / 1000).toFixed(1) : 'N/A'}B</div>
      <div class="stat-label">FY Revenue</div>
    </div>
    <div class="stat-card">
      <div class="stat-value">${fcfBase !== null ? (fcfBase / 1000).toFixed(1) : 'N/A'}B</div>
      <div class="stat-label">Free Cash Flow</div>
    </div>
    <div class="stat-card">
      <div class="stat-value">${epsCurrent !== null ? epsCurrent.toFixed(2) : 'N/A'}</div>
      <div class="stat-label">EPS (Diluted)</div>
    </div>
    <div class="stat-card">
      <div class="stat-value">${(netCash / 1000).toFixed(1)}B</div>
      <div class="stat-label">Net Cash</div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- ═══ METHODOLOGY ═══ -->
  <h2>Methodology: Two-Stage DCF</h2>
  <p>We use a <strong>two-stage discounted cash flow (DCF)</strong> model — the gold standard of intrinsic valuation. No multiples, no comparables, no vibes. Just future cash flows discounted to today.</p>

  <div class="method-step">
    <div class="step-num">1</div>
    <div class="step-content">
      <h4>Start with actual Free Cash Flow</h4>
      <p>S&P Global generated <strong>${(fcfBase / 1000).toFixed(2)} billion</strong> in free cash flow in the most recent fiscal year. This is real cash the business produces after paying for everything, including capital expenditures.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="method-step">
    <div class="step-num">2</div>
    <div class="step-content">
      <h4>Project FCF growth for 5 years (Phase 1)</h4>
      <p>We grow FCF at <strong>{(growthRatePhase1 * 100).toFixed(0)}% per year</strong> for 5 years. This reflects S&P Global's strong pricing power and oligopoly position in ratings and indices, providing steady top-line and bottom-line expansion.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="method-step">
    <div class="step-num">3</div>
    <div class="step-content">
      <h4>Calculate terminal value (Phase 2)</h4>
      <p>After Year 5, we assume FCF grows at <strong>{(growthRateTerminal * 100).toFixed(1)}% forever</strong>. We use the <strong>Gordon Growth Model</strong>: Terminal Value = FCF₆ ÷ (discount rate − terminal growth rate). This captures all value from Year 6 to infinity.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="method-step">
    <div class="step-num">4</div>
    <div class="step-content">
      <h4>Discount everything to present value</h4>
      <p>All future cash flows are discounted at <strong>{(discountRate * 100).toFixed(0)}%</strong> — our required rate of return. This is the cost of equity, factoring in a 4.18% 10Y Treasury yield, market risk premium, and SPGI's low relative volatility.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="method-step">
    <div class="step-num">5</div>
    <div class="step-content">
      <h4>Add net cash, divide by shares</h4>
      <p>Enterprise Value + Net Cash (${(netCash / 1000).toFixed(1)}B) = Equity Value. Divide by shares outstanding ({sharesOutstanding}M) for the per-share intrinsic value.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- ═══ THE THREE ASSUMPTIONS ═══ -->
  <h2>The Three Assumptions That Drive Everything</h2>
  <p>A DCF is only as good as its inputs. We're making exactly <strong>three</strong> judgment calls — everything else is math. Here's what we chose and why.</p>

  <div class="assumption-grid">
    <div class="assumption-card">
      <div class="label">FCF Growth Rate (Years 1-5)</div>
      <div class="value">{(growthRatePhase1 * 100).toFixed(0)}%</div>
      <div class="rationale">
        S&P Global has wide moats (network effects in ratings, brand value in indices). They routinely raise prices faster than inflation with little customer churn. We expect high-single-digit organic growth to translate nicely into 8% FCF growth.
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="assumption-card">
      <div class="label">Discount Rate (WACC)</div>
      <div class="value">{(discountRate * 100).toFixed(0)}%</div>
      <div class="rationale">
        10Y Treasury: 4.18%. With a beta close to 1.0 and a standard equity risk premium of ~5%, a 9% discount rate provides a solid hurdle rate for this high-quality, predictable business.
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="assumption-card">
      <div class="label">Terminal Growth Rate</div>
      <div class="value">{(growthRateTerminal * 100).toFixed(1)}%</div>
      <div class="rationale">
        Long-term nominal GDP growth is ~3%. We add 0.5% for S&P Global's structural advantages: the deeply entrenched nature of its credit ratings and global benchmarks. A 3.5% perpetuity growth rate is reasonable for an irreplaceable financial toll bridge.
